Adult.description: Adult White-throated Sparrows have a bright white throat patch and yellow between the bill and the eyes. They often look dingier or less crisp overall than White-crowned Sparrows.

Immature.description: Immature White-throated Sparrows have black stripes on the crown, instead of immature White-crowned's reddish stripes. They have a grayish, not yellowish, bill, and usually show a neat white throat patch.

Adult.description: Adult Golden-crowned Sparrows have no white on the head. The crown stripe is yellow, not white.

Immature.description: Immature Golden-crowned Sparrows usually have some yellow on the crown, helping to distinguish them from immature White-crowned Sparrows, which they closely resemble.

Female.description: Female House Sparrows are smaller, shorter tailed, and smaller billed, with an unmarked face and no white on the wing.
